headline: Persistent gaps in risk and adaptation strategies remain amid rising climate hazards
summary: NEW YORK, September 19, 2025--New research published today by Marsh, the world’s leading insurance broker and risk advisor and a business of Marsh McLennan (NYSE: MMC), reveals that while there is widespread acknowledgment of climate risks, organizations are not conducting comprehensive cost-benefit analyses to justify further adaptation investments. This is resulting in significant gaps between the outcome of climate risk assessments and adaptation strategies.
